We recommended and Management agreed that the:
General Services Officer or the designated Inventory Committee strictly conduct the periodic physical count of property, plant and equipment and submit to the Auditor, the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) of the City as of December 31 of each year, not later than January 31 of the following year;
General Services Officer and City Accountant regularly update property cards/ledgers and act promptly on discrepancies noted in the physical count;
General Services Officer update property inventory stickers during physical count;
General Services Officer update PARs in order that the new custodian of properties be reflected; and
General Services Officer maintain the Registry of Public Infrastructures (RPI) of road networks, flood control systems, water supply systems, parks, plazas and monuments and coordinate with the City Accountant to reconcile the PPE of ₱469.194 million as of December 31, 2020.

